36.body: Data class is like a class but implements for you: equals() and hashCode() toString() copy() Data class is the idiomatic way to define objects that contains only data. A common operation you would perform on data is comparison - this is where the equals function comes in handy. Note that data classes, however, do not translate to Java's Records. You need the @JvmRecord annotation.

}
val person = Person() person.age = 50
person.doThis()
person.thenThat()
val ageInTenDecades = futureAge(100) val ageInTenDecades = person.run { age = 50 doThis() thenThat() getFinalFutureAge(100)
